<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1006&amp;p=8645#p8645"><![CDATA[
Banks in NESasm are 8KB each, <strong>not</strong> 16KB.<br />This can be a significant annoyance, however, especially when you are working with a mapper which uses 16KB or 32KB banks, since it will generate an <em>error</em> (and refuse to assemble the program) if code/data crosses a bank boundary.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Thu Jan 26, 2006 3:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
