<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1006&amp;p=8644#p8644"><![CDATA[
Nesasm is really dumb with banks. One bank number is for the CHR data in a basic 8K CHR 16K PRG code in Nesasm. The other two are actually like this:<br /><br />Bank 0: $8000-$BFFF<br />Bank 1: $C000-$FFFF<br /><br />I believe it is like that. But I don't know exactly, I was having much trouble with that too. I never figured out how to use banks correctly with NESASM...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=138">Celius</a> — Thu Jan 26, 2006 3:16 pm</p><hr />
